UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0022199687900560
AB  - The paper investigates how domestic content requirements imposed on a vertically integrated monopolist affect production and welfare. Three content schemes are investigated. It is shown that a scheme can be formulated which increases the range of intermediate goods as well as the quantity of final good produced. This occurs even though the firms' production costs are invariably increased by content protection. The scheme can also increase domestic welfare.
