UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0022199687900559
AB  - This paper compares the relative efficiency of local content schemes and tariffs as alternative means of achieving certain non-economic/distributional objectives. The efficiency comparison is made under the alternative assumptions that an intermediate good/component is produced (a) competitively and (b) by a single firm. The paper shows how the ranking of tariffs and content schemes (i) is sensitive to these assumptions and (ii) depends on the local content ratio and the elasticity of demand for components. The possible implications of vertical integration in the production process and rent/revenue seeking behaviour are also considered insofar as they affect the ranking of policies.
ER  - 

