AB  - The paper analyses the implications for the timing and magnitude of a speculative attack on a fixed exchange rate of government borrowing to increase the stock of international reserves. It is shown that such borrowing reduces the likelihood of an early collapse and increases the likelihood of an eventual collapse. The magnitude of the speculative attack also increases.
