T1  - The equalization of factor prices in general equilibrium when commodities outnumber factors
AU  - Wu, Ho-mou
JO  - Journal of International Economics
VL  - 23
IS  - 3
SP  - 343
EP  - 356
PY  - 1987
DA  - 1987/11/01/
SN  - 0022-1996
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0022-1996(87)90060-2
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0022199687900602
AB  - The likelihood of factor price equalization is analyzed in a full general equilibrium model which incorporates the demand side and commodity market clearance. A method is developed to actually derive the cone of factor price equalization in a general equilibrium model with many commodities and two factors. This cone is then used to analyze the actual likelihood of equalization as a function of the underlying primitives such as endowment ratios and demand patterns in the economy. It can be determined quantitatively how similar endowment ratios should be in order to ensure equalization for different demand patterns.
ER  - 
